title: I'm new to this app so far... but, I loooove it already!!! :)
text: I'm new to this app so far... but, I loooove it already!!! :) This is an awesome community of people who are there for each other. You can set your status and other people can comment on it or hug you! Who doesn`t love a hug? lol. You can also keep track of your moods, etc. and see where the global mood (everyone that uses the application) is set for the day!!! :) It's interesting to see if you are having the same moods that everyone else is having! :) ALSO... I read reviews about the speed not being fast???.... I have an EXTREMELY slow tablet... BUT WHEN IT CAME TO THE SPEED OF THE APP... IT WAS VERY, VERY, VERY FAST!!! :)

title: annoying start up
text: annoying start up It's already annoying to have to sign up for something but on top of that if you click the login with facebook choice it doesn't automatically connect but opens the website within the MoodPanda app, which doesn't even load properly to allow me to enter my username.  It's very common for apps that allow login via facebook to connect directly to the app.  Get this functionality or better yet get rid of requirement for usernames.

title: Was great now Ok
text: Was great now Ok Loved that I had the option not to publish my inner self with the whole world & easily figured put privacy features.  Loved the graphs although some were hard to read & have no explanation on how to interpret. Newest upgrade didn't seem to improve but made SLOWER &I do not like that it no longer goes to a main menu. The window requesting donations everytime you update your status probably well annoy others but I understand.

title: Please Read
text: Please Read If you're thinking of downloading this app, I highly recommend you do. In my personal experience, it has saved my life and the support from the community is incomparable to any other. In the stories others have shared with me about MoodPanda, they say they are happy they found this because it has helped them in many ways. Pandas (what we call ourselves) are very caring, we understand the struggles of "mental illness" and how to help with it. You must try it.

title: Great!
text: Great! This is a very nice app for tracking my mood. I work on my depression in a variety of ways, and Mood Panda is just one of the tools I use. In my CBT therapy work we are encouraged to track our mood often. This is a great tool to do so.

title: Mood Panda? Why not Private?
text: Mood Panda? Why not Private? I do not like that it is not private, I know my diagnosis and have had many years of therapy, I just wanted a private journal that showed low and high(manic) days. It's harder because I don't get out at all due to illness. You should be able to pick a 1-10 face like at the dr. Or at leat rate 1-10. It's time consuming moving that bar.

title: Nice Idea, Horrible Implementation
text: Nice Idea, Horrible Implementation The app is slow. And I means SLOW. It takes a long time to load, a long time to log in, and a long time to do anything in it, not to mention the general slowness is made worse by popups asking for donations which add even more time to an already sluggish process. It's so bad that whenever I load the app to add my current mood, I feel like subtracting a point just for the poor app experience alone.  Were the app minimally fast and I'd give it 4 stars. As it is, I'm subtracting two points for the poor, sloooow user experience.  That said, if you limit yourself to loading the app once a day and no more, the slowness can be endured and its features enjoyed. Just do like me and tap the icon, turn off the screen, then a little later turn the screen back on to use the (now loaded) app.  PS.: If the developer fixes the slowness I'll come back and add more stars.
Terrible design, non-native app.  Please make a native, design-conscious app!
